{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b0427c68-fac8-459d-b9e0-9ed2e97ed81e","content":"Here's how to migrate your xUnit.net project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n**1. Update package references in your `.csproj`:**\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n<!-- Add -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform\" Version=\"1.0.0\" />\n```\n\n**2. Add the MSBuild property** (in `.csproj` or `Directory.Build.props`):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. Optionally enable the new output** (for `dotnet test`):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>true</GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**4. Run tests** with:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test\n# or directly:\ndotnet run --project YourTest.csproj\n```\n\nKey points:\n- Keep `xunit` 2.9.3 — it's compatible.\n- The runner package (`xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform`) replaces `xunit.runner.visualstudio`.\n- `dotnet test` still works; the new platform also lets you run the test project as an executable directly.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"89c40448-1dcf-4640-a330-b85efb65f249","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":409,"requestId":"E3DE:165513:16351F7:18CE630:6A051F91"},"id":"e18c7419-f709-401d-978e-11c4e1dd6663","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:04:26.599Z","parentId":"d7671b6c-1ab0-470e-8e52-db9478350383"}
